Americans' confidence in President Trump's leadership abilities has gone down over his first few months in office, new polls reveal. (Peter Stevenson/The Washington Post)

President Trump's setbacks on campaign promises such as repealing the Affordable Care Act and his shifting positions on other stances look like they're catching up with him — bigly.

A new poll from Gallup released early Monday finds that a majority of Americans no longer view Trump as keeping his promises, with poll numbers on that question falling from 62 percent in February to 45 percent in early April, a stunning tumble
